The paper deals with capacity analysis of interference channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Specifically, it focuses on many-to-one interference channels, which can be classified as network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses interference alignment, which is a technique used in signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper deals with MIMO and parallel Gaussian channels, which are topics in multimedia (cs.MM) and communication complexity (cs.CC), respectively.
